    "description": "This was spurred on by the experiences of a few folks attempting to use the modules that I wrote that use the astropy on-demand import. If they try to use them without having astropy installed, then they get a usually unhelpful error message, which doesn't really tell them what the problem is.   \r\n\r\nI've corrected this by adding a `NotAModule` class for the on-demand imports, which prints an error message if the needed underlying package is not installed, if someone tries to access anything from the module, e.g. `_astropy.pyfits`.\r\n\r\nI also added scipy to the list of on-demand imports, and fixed `na` -> `np` issues that I saw in `absorption_spectrum`. ",
